'''''Red Tail Reborn''''' is a 2007 historical documentary film by Adam White about the [[Commemorative Air Force]]'s [[Red Tail Project]].  The project involves the restoration, exhibition and maintenance of a [[World War II]] [[P-51 Mustang]] flown by the [[United States Air Force]] [[332d Fighter Group]].  The exhibition of this plane is considered to be a traveling and flying tribute to the [[Tuskegee Airmen]].  The film was initially broadcast and released on [[DVD]] in the director's home state of Ohio, winning local [[Emmy Award]] recognition.  Eventually, it was broadcast nationally on [[Public Broadcasting Services]] (PBS) stations. In addition to increasing awareness of the travails of the Tuskegee Airmen, this film served to highlight the Red Tail Project fundraising effort to rebuild the plane after a 2004 crash.  The film had a sequel called ''[[Flight of the Red Tail]]''.

